                    Read Me


*******************************************************
*  Problem description
*******************************************************

Implement the following algorithms using SageMath tool

   - Affine cipher
   - Hill cipher
   - Shift cipher
   - Substitution cipher
   - Transposition cipher
   - Vigenere cipher

This should be followed by cryptanalysis of all the above
classical cyphers algorithm from 1 - 6.

*******************************************************
*  Circumstances of programs
*******************************************************

    This program works and runs as intended.

    Implemented the cipher techniques followed by the breaking
    of the ciphers or cryptanalysis.

    The program was tested on :
    Python 3.8.5
    SageMath version 9.0


*******************************************************
*  How to build and run the program
*******************************************************

1. Each cipher is written as a module inside a package with the
   name of the package resembling the cipher technique.

2. Run the Python module runner command outside the
   `classical_ciphers` folder:
   
        python3 -m classical_ciphers.<cipher_package_name>.<cipher_module_name>

        E.g. python3 -m classical_ciphers.shift.shift_cipher

